1
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:04,200
<i>Please don't see Rintarô again.</i>

2
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:09,500
<i>I'm sure she's feeling screwy
to find out that I'm her father.</i>

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:14,000
<i>Please let her keep
her happiness.</i>

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,200
<i>Leave.</i>

5
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:23,100
<i>Marimo!</i>

6
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:46,130
So it's just a cold.

7
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:48,900
She gave me a scare!

8
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:53,010
She must've worn herself
out from everything.

9
00:00:53,670 --> 00:00:57,640
With Rintarô-kun and
Sotokoba-san.

10
00:00:59,050 --> 00:01:01,650
It must've hit her
all at once.

11
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:05,550
A lot has been going
on for you, too.

12
00:01:06,650 --> 00:01:08,690
<i>What do you take your
parental responsibilities as?</i>

13
00:01:08,690 --> 00:01:10,320
<i>That has nothing
to do with it!</i>

14
00:01:14,130 --> 00:01:16,900
How about beef with
potatoes and rolled eggs?

15
00:01:17,870 --> 00:01:19,570
What is it?

16
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:23,670
You haven't cooked
for me in a long time.

17
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,110
Well, the situation isn't
the same as before.

18
00:01:32,010 --> 00:01:34,310
I feel like a youth now.

19
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:38,220
Stop it. I'm cooking now.

20
00:01:40,690 --> 00:01:42,790
I don't believe this.

21
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:46,560
I want to use the bathroom.

22
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:56,900
It's making me sick!

23
00:01:59,740 --> 00:02:02,640
I'm sorry. I want
to use the bathroom.

24
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:11,720
Isn't that awful? I'm lying
in bed with a cold.

25
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:16,290
But those two were
getting it on together.

26
00:02:16,290 --> 00:02:17,760
Can you believe that?

27
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:20,000
So I yelled and stopped
them in the act.

28
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,760
Is that right?

29
00:02:22,230 --> 00:02:24,500
So you broke the
two up in the act?

30
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:27,730
- Isn't that improper?
- What did Dr. Asami do?

31
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:29,560
She left a while later.

32
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:33,780
Is that right? So you
chased her out.

33
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:35,780
Don't say it like that.

34
00:02:36,410 --> 00:02:38,780
Is that right?

35
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:41,740
The little devil picked on
her future stepmother.

36
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:43,820
Don't say it like that.

37
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,220
Never mind already.

38
00:02:49,660 --> 00:02:53,360
That's the face of a
daughter who is jealous

39
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,970
that her father is getting
close to the woman he loves.

40
00:02:55,970 --> 00:02:58,470
Is that right?

41
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:01,400
You're not saying it right.

42
00:03:02,270 --> 00:03:04,140
Try it again.

43
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:08,510
We're in the semi-finals now!

44
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:15,180
We have a full stadium with
an audience of 54,000!

45
00:03:17,380 --> 00:03:19,250
And the throws!

46
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,650
He just gave a glare!

47
00:03:22,590 --> 00:03:24,560
The coach gives an order!

48
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:27,230
And he throws!

49
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:31,800
- What do you think of that?
- What do you mean?

50
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,200
Did I get across the
feelings of the Yokohama

51
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,430
team and their coach?

52
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:37,000
There's a <i>mamono</i>
at the Kôshien.

53
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,210
- There's a <i>marimo</i>?
- Not <i>marimo</i> but <i>mamono</i>!

54
00:03:41,540 --> 00:03:43,750
Don't you youngsters get it?

55
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:46,680
Love.

56
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:49,850
Do you understand?

57
00:03:49,850 --> 00:03:54,120
That's right. Coach Watanabe's
love for his students is in

58
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:57,520
that single ball. The coach
said something good...

59
00:03:57,860 --> 00:04:00,390
Is that right?

60
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:05,230
They're on the same
wavelength...

61
00:04:10,270 --> 00:04:14,410
<i>Those two were trying
to be lovey-dovey...</i>

62
00:04:16,110 --> 00:04:20,380
Does that mean...
that I interrupted?

63
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:25,420
Oh, no. That makes it
hard for me to stay here.

64
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:30,060
I got lucky!

65
00:04:30,490 --> 00:04:33,260
I got an overnight
onsen trip for two.

66
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:36,330
I won it in the lottery
for the shopping district.

67
00:04:36,330 --> 00:04:38,300
A onsen trip? How nice!

68
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:40,600
- Get ready.
- Serious?

69
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,700
It'll make a nice memory
for this summer.

70
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:45,070
- Let's have a grand time!
- Are we going from now?

71
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:51,340
On second thought, I'll pass.

72
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:53,880
You should go with Asami-san.

73
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:56,080
Yes, go with Asami-san!

74
00:04:56,850 --> 00:04:59,020
You're blushing!

75
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,500
I want to take you.

76
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:07,110
No! Why do I have to go
with you to the onsen?

77
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:09,620
I don't want to share
a room with you!

78
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:12,800
What's the difference
from here?

79
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:15,000
There's a curtain to
separate our areas!

80
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,680
Stop talking back!
Just get ready!

81
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:21,170
- No one's home!
- It's me, Rintarô!

82
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,290
You left home?

83
00:05:24,290 --> 00:05:27,350
I had a fight with my
dad and I left home.

84
00:05:27,350 --> 00:05:32,080
I figured Shinpei-san would
understand how I feel.

85
00:05:32,490 --> 00:05:34,830
I'm sorry for barging
my way in.

86
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:37,240
<i>Rintarô-senpai came
to our house.</i>

87
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:39,810
<i>It appears that he might
end up living with us.</i>

88
00:05:39,810 --> 00:05:42,790
<i>My summer is about
to take a sudden turn...</i>

89
00:05:42,790 --> 00:05:48,940
No. Go home. Your
parents must be worried.

90
00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:54,470
It's an inconvenience. Go.

91
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:08,120
What is he thinking
of anyway?

92
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:10,390
This isn't a shelter
for runaways.

93
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:12,330
Why aren't you
helping him?

94
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:15,320
- Why should I?
- He's in a bind.

95
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:18,230
I know! You want
to live with him here.

96
00:06:18,230 --> 00:06:22,270
- You have such a dirty mind!
- Never mind already.

97
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:30,180
What's with her?

98
00:06:30,810 --> 00:06:34,610
<i>What's with him?
He sure upsets me.</i>

99
00:06:45,890 --> 00:06:48,070
You're doing
the same thing!

100
